12/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and her Croatian counterpart, Tonino Picula, jointly called for clearer perspectives on EU integration of the countries in the region.Following their meeting in Skopje on Friday (10 January), the two diplomats confirmed that the Euro-Atlantic integration remained a priority for both Macedonia and Croatia. 
They expressed hope that the forthcoming EU summit in Thessaloniki would result in a clear vision for the EU future of Southeast European states. 
Mitreva and Picula also said that the trilateral co-operation among Macedonia, Croatia and Albania would boost the process of NATO integration. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Vest - 11/01/03; MIA - 12/01/03)
